    "# Electric V-BAT Tail-Sitter — Conceptual Sizing Study\n",
    "### Autonomous Vehicle Research Platform \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose.** This notebook performs a first-principles conceptual sizing of a small electric\n",
    "tail-sitter VTOL UAV.  The goal is to answer the core feasibility question:\n",
    "\n",
    "> *What must the aircraft weigh, and how large must its battery and wing be,\n",
    ">  to carry a research payload for a specified duration?*\n",
    "\n",
    "All physics lives in `src/conceptual_design/`.  This notebook **only sets parameters,\n",
    "calls modules, and interprets results.**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Notebook Structure\n",
    "\n",
    "| Section | What it does |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| 0 · Setup | Imports and path configuration |\n",
    "| 1 · Mission & Requirements | Define what the UAV must do |\n",
    "| 2 · Design Parameters | Aerodynamics, propulsion, battery, structure |\n",
    "| 3 · Forward Flight Analysis | Size Matching Diagram — optimal wing loading |\n",
    "| 4 · VTOL Power Analysis | Hover and climb power-to-weight |\n",
    "| 5 · Mass Closure Loop | Iteratively solve for MTOW |\n",
    "| 6 · Sensitivity Analysis | How assumptions affect the result |\n",
    "| 7 · Design Summary | Final mass budget, geometry, verdict |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
