  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4 · VTOL Power Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "### Theory\n",
    "\n",
    "In vertical flight, the power budget has three physically distinct\n",
    "contributions (Jae-Hyun et al., eqs. 2-61 to 2-64):\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Induced + climb power — work done accelerating air downward through the\n",
    "   rotor disk.  From actuator disk (momentum) theory:\n",
    "\n",
    "       P_induced/W = RoC/2  +  (1/2) * sqrt(RoC^2 + 2*DL/rho)\n",
    "\n",
    "   At hover (RoC = 0) this collapses to P/W = sqrt(DL / 2*rho), divided\n",
    "   by FoM to account for real rotor losses.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. Profile drag power — energy wasted dragging rotor blades through air:\n",
    "\n",
    "       P_profile/W = rho * Vtip^3 * sigma * CD_blade / (8 * DL)\n",
    "\n",
    "   where  Vtip = pi * RPM * D / 60\n",
    "   and    RPM  = 2762.8 * D^(-0.932)   (empirical, eq. 2-64)\n",
    "\n",
    "3. Parasite drag terms — body and wing drag in the vertical airstream:\n",
    "\n",
    "       C1 = rho * RoC^3 / DL\n",
    "       C2 = rho * RoC^3 / (S_ratio * WL)\n",
    "\n",
    "The Figure of Merit (FoM ~= 0.70) represents real rotor efficiency:\n",
    "swirl losses, tip losses, non-uniform inflow relative to ideal actuator\n",
    "disk.  A well-designed rotor achieves FoM 0.72–0.80.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Build VTOLParams from prop config\n",
    "vtol_p = VTOLParams.from_propulsive(prop, env)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Rotor geometry\n",
    "rpm     = rpm_from_diameter(D_rotor_m, vtol_p)\n",
    "Vtip    = vtip_from_rpm_and_diameter(rpm, D_rotor_m)\n",
    "S_rotor = np.pi * (D_rotor_m / 2)**2\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Rotor geometry:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Diameter    : {D_rotor_m*100:.0f} cm\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Disk area   : {S_rotor:.4f} m²\")\n",
    "print(f\"  RPM         : {rpm:.0f} rpm  (eq. 2-64)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Tip speed   : {Vtip:.1f} m/s  (eq. 2-63)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Disk loading: {disk_loading:.0f} N/m²\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── P/W over range of disk loadings\n",
    "DL_range = np.linspace(60, 350, 400)\n",
    "PW_hover = np.array([vtol_hover_power_to_weight(dl, vtol_p) for dl in DL_range])\n",
    "PW_climb = np.array([vtol_climb_power_to_weight(\n",
    "    mission.rate_of_climb, dl, smd.WS_design, D_rotor_m, vtol_p) for dl in DL_range])\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Term decomposition at the design disk loading\n",
    "dl        = disk_loading\n",
    "A_induced = 0.5 * mission.rate_of_climb + 0.5 * np.sqrt(\n",
    "              mission.rate_of_climb**2 + 2*dl/env.rho)\n",
    "B_profile = (env.rho * Vtip**3 * vtol_p.sigma * vtol_p.CD_blade) / (8.0 * dl)\n",
    "C1_paras  = (env.rho * mission.rate_of_climb**3) / dl\n",
    "C2_paras  = (env.rho * mission.rate_of_climb**3) / (vtol_p.S_ratio * smd.WS_design)\n",
    "total_pw  = A_induced + B_profile + C1_paras + C2_paras\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"P/W term breakdown at DL={disk_loading:.0f} N/m², RoC={mission.rate_of_climb} m/s:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  A. Induced + climb  : {A_induced:.4f} W/N  ({A_induced/total_pw*100:.1f}%)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  B. Profile drag     : {B_profile:.4f} W/N  ({B_profile/total_pw*100:.1f}%)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  C1. Fuselage paras  : {C1_paras:.4f} W/N  ({C1_paras/total_pw*100:.1f}%)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  C2. Wing parasite   : {C2_paras:.4f} W/N  ({C2_paras/total_pw*100:.1f}%)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Total               : {total_pw:.4f} W/N\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Plot VTOL P/W vs disk loading\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(11, 4.5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Left: P/W curves vs disk loading\n",
    "ax = axes[0]\n",
    "ax.plot(DL_range, PW_hover, color=COLORS[0], lw=2.0, label='Hover  (RoC = 0)')\n",
    "ax.plot(DL_range, PW_climb, color=COLORS[1], lw=2.0, ls='--',\n",
    "        label=f'Climb  (RoC = {mission.rate_of_climb} m/s)')\n",
    "ax.axvline(disk_loading, color='gray', lw=1.2, ls=':',\n",
    "           label=f'Design DL = {disk_loading:.0f} N/m²')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Disk loading  W/S_rotor  [N/m²]', fontsize=10)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('P/W  [W/N]', fontsize=10)\n",
    "ax.set_title('VTOL Power-to-Weight vs Disk Loading', fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Right: term breakdown pie at design disk loading\n",
    "ax2 = axes[1]\n",
    "terms      = [A_induced, B_profile, C1_paras, C2_paras]\n",
    "labels     = ['Induced\\n+ climb', 'Blade\\nprofile',\n",
    "              'Fuselage\\nparasite', 'Wing\\nparasite']\n",
    "colors_pie = [COLORS[0], COLORS[1], COLORS[2], COLORS[3]]\n",
    "wedges, texts, autotexts = ax2.pie(\n",
    "    terms, labels=labels, colors=colors_pie,\n",
    "    autopct='%1.0f%%', startangle=90, textprops={'fontsize': 9}\n",
    ")\n",
    "for at in autotexts:\n",
    "    at.set_fontsize(9)\n",
    "ax2.set_title(f'P/W Term Breakdown at DL={disk_loading:.0f} N/m²',\n",
    "              fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('vtol_power_analysis.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nKey insight: induced power dominates (~90% of total).\")\n",
    "print(\"Increasing disk loading (smaller rotor) raises hover power non-linearly — sqrt(DL).\")\n",
    "print(\"This is the fundamental argument for large rotors in hover-heavy missions.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5 · Mass Closure — Iterative MTOW Sizing\n",
    "\n",
    "### The Circular Dependency\n",
    "\n",
    "The core challenge in electric aircraft design is that every component\n",
    "affects the MTOW, and the MTOW drives the battery requirement:\n",
    "\n",
    "    m_total = m_payload + m_battery + f_fixed * m_total    (f_fixed = 0.55)\n",
    "\n",
    "Re-arranging gives the closed-form MTOW for a given battery mass:\n",
    "\n",
    "    m_total = (m_payload + m_battery) / (1 - f_fixed)\n",
    "\n",
    "But the battery mass depends on the mission energy, which depends on the\n",
    "power, which depends on MTOW:\n",
    "\n",
    "    m_battery = E_req / (e_spec * eta_bat * f_usable)\n",
    "\n",
    "    E_req = f_res * ( P_hover*t_hover/3600  +  P_cruise*t_cruise/3600 )\n",
    "\n",
    "where  P_hover  = (P/W)_hover  * m_total * g\n",
    "  and  P_cruise = m_total * g * V_cruise / (L/D * eta_total)\n",
    "\n",
    "The loop converges because the battery mass function is a contraction\n",
    "mapping — each iteration brings m_battery closer to the fixed point."
   ]
  }
 ],
